oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Olive green wool puttees
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This pair of puttees are made of dark olive green knit wool. They are in excellent condition. Puttees were wrapped around lower legs to protect from mud and water. This pair belonged to Albert S. Bridges, 329th Inf. Regt., 165th Brig., 83rd Div. Discharged January 5, 1919.
